snippet.textDisplay: Tickets did not sell out within minutes/days/ or a week. They still have a couple hundred non resale tickets available at t mobile arena website. What happened to make you think they sold out is when they wen't on sale there were so many people on the site it said you had to wait your turn. Then when I got in to purchase said there were no tickets. Not sold out because when you select a ticket you have 2 minutes to buy or they get released back to the public. So it was basically a shit ton of people that had all the tickets locked up. For the 1st hour or so then it kind of leveled off. I had to spam refresh "Oh no, no seats are available" about 10 times to be able to get a shot at tickets somebody didn't end up buying after the 2 minute hold. After about 30 minutes i finally was able to get a decent ticket that i bought that i have forsale Section 13 row b seat 6. Since everybody had them locked up (2 mins repeated over by thousands of people) you just had to spam refresh and it would give you a random ticket somebody released. You'd then  have to look at the map and see where it was and if you wanted it. If not just keep repeating the process. Spam refresh on find tickets, if not a good one release it back. Now that there isn't thousands of people on the site locking up the tickets you can actually see whats left and get to pick. But they are not sold out. That be some bs lol
